// @test regression/INV135-cast-return-qualifier
// @description Builtin casts preserve the strongest argument qualifier in return inference. Probed 2026-06-28, see investigations/INV135-cast-return-qualifier/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects error: line=5, column=12, message=/Cannot call "f" with argument "n"="x".*An argument of "series int" type was used but a "simple int"/
// @expects error: line=6, column=13, message=/Cannot call "f" with argument "n"="call "int" \(series int\)".*An argument of "series int" type was used but a "simple int"/
// @expects errors: 2
//@version=6
indicator("INV135")
x = int(close)
f(simple int n) => n
badVar = f(x)
badCall = f(int(close))
ok = f(int(5))
plot(badVar + badCall + ok)
